stimulus:
Welcome!

We are Dean McHugh and Tomasz Klochowicz from the University of Amsterdam. At the beginning, we would like to thank you for your participation in this study. It should take you no more than 15 minutes to answer all the questions.

The questions do not have "right" or "wrong" answers. Some of the questions may seem similar, but please answer all of them. The survey does not aim to test your general knowledge. Some of the questions may refer to real people or events, but the stories in the questions are completely made up for the sole purpose of this survey. If a story seems false or implausible to you, try to imagine the situation described by the story. If you have any questions, you can contact us by e-mail at: t.j.klochowicz@uva.nl.

Informed Consent

By clicking the button 'Accept and continue' below you declare that:

You have been clearly informed about the research: Similarity and Aboutness in Conditionals, research project conducted by Tomasz Klochowicz (PhD student) and Dean McHugh (postdoc) at the University of Amsterdam, Institute for Logic Language and Computation, as described in the information brochure displayed at prolific.co. You declare that your questions have been answered to your satisfaction.

You realise that participation in this research is on an entirely voluntary basis. You retain the right to revoke this consent without having to provide any reasons for my decision. You are aware that you are entitled to discontinue the research at any time, and that you can always withdraw your consent after the research has ended. If you decide to stop or withdraw your consent, all the information gathered up until then will be permanently deleted.

If your data are used in scientific publications or made public in any other way, they will be fully anonymised. Your personal information may not be viewed by third parties.

If you need any further information on the research, now or in the future, you can contact Tomasz Klochowicz (email: t.j.klochowicz@uva.nl) or Dean McHugh (d.m.mchugh@uva.nl); Universiteit van Amsterdam P.O. Box 94242 1090 GE Amsterdam.

If you have any complaints regarding this research, you can contact the secretary of the Ethics Committee of the Faculty of Humanities of the University of Amsterdam; email: commissie-ethiek-fgw@uva.nl; phone number: +31 20 525 3054; Binnengasthuisstraat 9, 1012 ZA Amsterdam.
